  "title": "PART TIME STUDENT CARE JUNIOR TRAINER",
  "description": "<p><strong>PART-TIME STUDENT CARE JUNIOR TRAINER</strong><br />Hougang Ave 1 & 5 | From $11/hr | Working with kids</p><p>Looking for a meaningful part-time job?<br />Enjoy working with children and want something stable with growth?<br />We’re hiring Junior Trainers to join our student care centre.</p><p><strong>Pay & Growth</strong></p><ul><li>Starting pay: $11/hour</li><li>Performance reviews twice a year (June & December)</li><li>Reviews include rewards, incentives & recognition (yes, even for part-timers!)</li><li>1-year commitment → eligible for increment & progression to Senior Trainer</li></ul><p><strong>What You’ll Do</strong></p><ul><li>Pick up students from school</li><li>Oversee meal times</li><li>Supervise homework, revision and activity</li><li>Communicate with parents via app</li><li>Provide guidance & discipline</li></ul><p>This is student care supervision, NOT tuition.</p><p><strong>Shifts Available</strong></p><ul><li>12.30pm – 6.30pm / 7.00pm</li><li>1.15pm – 6.15pm</li><li>Flexible shifts available if you have other commitments</li></ul><p>Minimum: 1 to 3 days / week</p><p><strong>We’re Looking For Someone Who Is:</strong></p><ul><li>Proactive & responsible</li><li>Caring and patient with children</li><li>Firm in discipline & classroom management</li><li>Efficient in homework checking & updates</li></ul><p><strong>Suitable for:</strong></p><ul><li>Fresh O-Level grads</li><li>Polytechnic / private diploma students</li><li>University students (local or private)</li><li>Young parents / caregivers looking for short, flexible hours</li><li>Anyone seeking a side-line or part-time work</li></ul><p><strong>How to Apply</strong><br />WhatsApp 9489 3552 with:</p><ul><li>Name</li><li>Age</li><li>Gender</li><li>Race</li><li>Languages spoken</li><li>Languages written</li><li>Highest Qualification</li><li>School course (if studying)</li><li>Graduation date (if studying)</li><li>PSLE score</li><li>Commitment period</li></ul><p>PRs & candidates with valid work passes welcome.<br />If you like working with kids and want a part-time role that actually values commitment — come join us!</p>",
